<section version="5.0"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://www.docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
    xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mth="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
    xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <title>Create an attribute</title>
    <para>To create a new metadata attribute and
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160627T111518+0200" comment="For SME: What is the exact action?
Assign an attribute to an object?
"?>add<?oxy_comment_end?>
        it to an object:</para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Attribute</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add button.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, type the name of the
                attribute.</para>
            <para>Each attribute must have a unique name</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Value type</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>If the value supplied for the attribute does not match the value type you will get
                a warning.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160627T110559+0200" comment="For SME: Mandatory?"?>Select<?oxy_comment_end?>
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160627T113528+0200" comment="For SME:
Removed this text:
Next, select which object (or objects) the attribute should be assigned to.
Is it correct that this is done via option sets?"?>an<?oxy_comment_end?>
                <emphasis role="bold">Option set </emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select the
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160627T111113+0200" comment="At next release:
Expand explanations to all the possible attributes." flag="done"?><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160627T111346+0200" comment="For SME: What do you select? Options? Objects?" mid="5"?>options<?oxy_comment_end?><?oxy_comment_end mid="5"?>
                you want, for example:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Mandatory</emphasis> if you want an object to
                        always have the dynamic attribute.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Select <emphasis role="bold">Unique</emphasis> if you want the system to
                        enforce that values are unique for a specific object type.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>The dynamic attribute is now available for the objects you assigned it to.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>

